nodes.documentation:
@dev Implementation of Multi-Token Standard contract. This implementation of the MT standard exploit the fact that
     balances of different token ids can be concatenated within individual uint256 storage slots.
     This allows the contract to batch transfer tokens more efficiently at the cost of limiting the 
     maximum token balance each address can hold. This limit is 2^IDS_BITS_SIZE, which can be 
     adjusted below. In practice, using IDS_BITS_SIZE smaller than 16 did not lead to major 
     efficiency gains. This token contract tries to adhere to ERC-1055 standard, but currently
     diverges from it as the standard is currently being constructed.

devdoc.details: Implementation of Multi-Token Standard contract. This implementation of the MT standard exploit the fact that     balances of different token ids can be concatenated within individual uint256 storage slots.     This allows the contract to batch transfer tokens more efficiently at the cost of limiting the      maximum token balance each address can hold. This limit is 2^IDS_BITS_SIZE, which can be      adjusted below. In practice, using IDS_BITS_SIZE smaller than 16 did not lead to major      efficiency gains. This token contract tries to adhere to ERC-1055 standard, but currently     diverges from it as the standard is currently being constructed.

balanceOf(address,uint256).return: Amount of objects of a given id ID

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: Get the balance of multiple account/token pairs

params._owners: The addresses of the token holders

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).return: The _owner's balance of the Token types requested

getIDBinIndex(uint256).details: Return the bin number and index within that bin where ID is
getIDBinIndex(uint256).return: (Bin number, ID"s index within that bin)

params._binValue: uint256 containing the balances of IDS_PER_UINT256 ids
params._index: index at which to retrieve value

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Function that verifies whether _operator is an authorized operator of _tokenHolder.

params._operator: The address of the operator to query status of

isApprovedForAll(address,address).return: A uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender.

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: transfer objects from different ids to specified address

params._data: Data to pass to onERC1155Received() function if recipient is contract Note:  Arrays should be sorted so that all ids in a same bin are adjacent (more efficient). IMRPOVEMENT : Could be simplified if EIP-1283 (https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1283) is implemented
params._from: The address to batchTransfer objects from.
params._ids: Array of ids to update balance of
params._to: The address to batchTransfer objects to.
params._values: Array of amount of object per id to be transferred.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Allow _from or an operator to transfer tokens from one address to another

params._data: Data to pass to onERC1155Received() function if recipient is contract
params._from: The address which you want to send tokens from
params._id: Token id to update balance of
params._to: The address which you want to transfer to
params._value: The amount of tokens of provided token ID to be transferred

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Will set _operator operator status to true or false

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Query if a contract implements an interface

params._interfaceID: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC-165

writeValueInBin(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: return the updated _binValue after writing _value at _index

params._binValue: uint256 containing the balances of IDS_PER_UINT256 ids
params._index: Index at which to retrieve value
